<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2 ext-discussiontools-init-section"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONDESKTOP__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-MessedRocker's_Rules-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;replies&quot;:[&quot;c-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z-MessedRocker's_Rules&quot;],&quot;text&quot;:&quot;MessedRocker's Rules&quot;,&quot;linkableTitle&quot;:&quot;MessedRocker's Rules&quot;}--><h2 data-mw-thread-id="h-MessedRocker&#039;s_Rules-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z"><span id="MessedRocker.27s_Rules"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="MessedRocker's_Rules"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-MessedRocker's_Rules-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z"></span>MessedRocker's Rules<span data-mw-comment-end="h-MessedRocker's_Rules-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:If_you_could_re-write_the_rules&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: MessedRocker&#039;s Rules"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"headingLevel":2,"name":"h-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z","type":"heading","level":0,"id":"h-MessedRocker's_Rules-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z","replies":["c-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z-MessedRocker's_Rules"]}}--><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-bar"><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-metadata"><!--__DTLATESTCOMMENTTHREAD__{"id":"c-41.114.80.209-2022-03-16T09:53:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z","timestamp":"2022-03-16T09:53:00.000Z"}__--><!--__DTCOMMENTCOUNT__3__--><!--__DTAUTHORCOUNT__3__--></div><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-actions"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONMOBILE__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-MessedRocker's_Rules-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;replies&quot;:[&quot;c-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z-MessedRocker's_Rules&quot;],&quot;text&quot;:&quot;MessedRocker's Rules&quot;,&quot;linkableTitle&quot;:&quot;MessedRocker's Rules&quot;}--></div></div></div>
<p><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z-MessedRocker's_Rules"></span>This probably won't cover every nook and cranny, but should I overlook anything, I would hope that these rules would inspire the rest. This also delves a bit into community practices which are not necessarily rules.
</p>
<ol><li><b>Some original research allowed</b> - Only when everyone with a functioning brain would come to the same  conclusion. Otherwise, let's have Wikipedia continue to be a passive relay of existing knowledge.</li>
<li><b>No pre-emptive blocks</b> - they give Wikipedia a bad reputation, and they really shun the culture of letting people participate. Really, how would you like to blocked because you violated some social custom you didn't know about? I'd feel like the guy who whistled at the wrong woman.</li>
<li><b>Template messages should seem like natural text</b> - Personally I would be in favor of getting rid of template messages entirely, but that would be annoying. Let's compromise by making them look like actual messages someone would post.</li>
<li><b>Stop obsessing over MySpacers</b>, as we have pejoratively labeled them because Lord Almighty forbid people enjoy using a website to socialize. No, this is Wikipedia. This is serious motherfucking business, and don't you forget it, or I will condemn you to live in New Jersey. (Greatly sorry, New Jersey.) End this prosecution of victimless crime, because for all you know they might be interested in doing some actual work once they've been acculturated to Wikipedia. This is relevant because I know of a website where they allow all sorts of fun and socializing, and it has only encouraged me to participate on the real work).</li>
<li><b>Hyphens!</b> - Sorry, I had to say something. Hyphens are on my keyboard; the two varieties of dashes are not.
<dl><dd>They are, they just require between 3 and 5 keypresses depending on your OS :) -- <a href="/wiki/User:Gurch" title="User:Gurch">Gurch</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Gurch" title="User talk:Gurch">talk</a>) 13:53, 3 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z-MessedRocker's_Rules"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z","author":"Gurch","type":"comment","level":1,"id":"c-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z-MessedRocker's_Rules","replies":["c-41.114.80.209-2022-03-16T09:53:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z","c-Iridescent-2009-01-06T02:23:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z-MessedRocker's_Rules"></span></dd>
<dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-41.114.80.209-2022-03-16T09:53:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z"></span>Halo <a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/41.114.80.209" title="Special:Contributions/41.114.80.209">41.114.80.209</a> (<a href="/w/index.php?title=User_talk:41.114.80.209&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="User talk:41.114.80.209 (page does not exist)">talk</a>) 09:53, 16 March 2022 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-41.114.80.209-2022-03-16T09:53:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2022-03-16T09:53:00.000Z","author":"41.114.80.209","type":"comment","level":3,"id":"c-41.114.80.209-2022-03-16T09:53:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-41.114.80.209-2022-03-16T09:53:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z"></span></dd></dl></li>
<li><b><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Iridescent-2009-01-06T02:23:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z"></span>Implement then evaluate</b> - All this hardcore discussion before we change any part of our policies or procedures is pretty hypocritical. If we had such a discussion when founding Wikipedia, it would have never been made. Since most things are reversible, it is a better idea to try something and <i>then</i> see if something is good not just on paper but in practice.</li></ol>
<p>I can't think of anything else right now. Please, I want other people's input. If I was the only one writing rules, you would absolutely despise my incumbency as a legislator.
</p><p>(As an aside, that comment left by that banned user was greatly amusing. I enjoyed reading it. Too bad s/he's banned.)
</p>
<dl><dd>That was <a href="/wiki/User:Moulton" title="User:Moulton">Moulton</a>. Believe me, now you've got his attention I dare say you'll be hearing a lot more than you ever wanted to hear about the Evil Conspiracy against him in which everyone involved behaves Just Like The Nazis in their attempts to stifle his advocacy of the Pre Hammurabic System. (Or maybe he's against the PHC and Wikipedia and the Nazis are for it – I don't think anyone's ever read one of his posts all the way through to find out.) If you're really lucky, he'll share some of his song lyrics with you. – <i><a href="/wiki/User:Iridescent" class="mw-redirect" title="User:Iridescent"><font color="#E45E05">iride</font><font color="#C1118C">scent</font></a></i> 02:23, 6 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Iridescent-2009-01-06T02:23:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-06T02:23:00.000Z","author":"Iridescent","type":"comment","level":2,"id":"c-Iridescent-2009-01-06T02:23:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Iridescent-2009-01-06T02:23:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:53:00.000Z"></span></dd></dl>
<p>Everyone starts editing this page but the fact is how much you edit that much it will become successful
