<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2 ext-discussiontools-init-section"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONDESKTOP__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-Stifle-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-Majorly's_rules-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;replies&quot;:[&quot;c-Messedrocker-2009-01-04T18:16:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules&quot;,&quot;c-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules&quot;,&quot;c-Stifle-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules&quot;,&quot;c-Ipatrol-2009-04-05T23:12:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules&quot;],&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Majorly's rules&quot;,&quot;linkableTitle&quot;:&quot;Majorly's rules&quot;}--><h2 data-mw-thread-id="h-Majorly&#039;s_rules-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z"><span id="Majorly.27s_rules"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Majorly's_rules"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-Majorly's_rules-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z"></span>Majorly's rules<span data-mw-comment-end="h-Majorly's_rules-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:If_you_could_re-write_the_rules&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Majorly&#039;s rules"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"headingLevel":2,"name":"h-Stifle-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z","type":"heading","level":0,"id":"h-Majorly's_rules-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z","replies":["c-Messedrocker-2009-01-04T18:16:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules","c-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules","c-Stifle-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules","c-Ipatrol-2009-04-05T23:12:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules"]}}--><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-bar"><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-metadata"><!--__DTLATESTCOMMENTTHREAD__{"id":"c-Ipatrol-2009-04-05T23:12:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules","timestamp":"2009-04-05T23:12:00.000Z"}__--><!--__DTCOMMENTCOUNT__11__--><!--__DTAUTHORCOUNT__7__--></div><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-actions"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONMOBILE__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-Stifle-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-Majorly's_rules-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;replies&quot;:[&quot;c-Messedrocker-2009-01-04T18:16:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules&quot;,&quot;c-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules&quot;,&quot;c-Stifle-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules&quot;,&quot;c-Ipatrol-2009-04-05T23:12:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules&quot;],&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Majorly's rules&quot;,&quot;linkableTitle&quot;:&quot;Majorly's rules&quot;}--></div></div></div>
<ul><li><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Messedrocker-2009-01-04T18:16:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules"></span>Editors who are continuously miserable put a downer on the atmosphere - until they can learn to work with others positively, they should either remove themselves from the project, or be banned if they cannot co-operate. If someone is not enjoying editing Wikipedia, they should stop editing it. People are here out of choice, and it seems nonsensical to come here if they're just going to go round in a grumpy mood all day, spoiling other people's leisure time.</li>
<li>Abolish RFA and split the tools up. Grant via a rollback like process, and give admins ability to remove. Remove admins' rights after they are inactive for three months, or after a community vote if there is abuse.</li>
<li>Abolish 3RR as a useless concept.</li>
<li>Allow articles to be rated by the most important people on this website - its readers. Abolish FAs and GAs, and all other kinds of class of article, which are essentially badge-gaining exercises. What's wrong with improving articles for no reward at the end? Allow the readers to rate the article, and the result is shown somewhere which gives people an idea of the quality.
<ul><li>Some of those things probably motivate people to write. Who <i>doesn't</i> want to have a star on their user page? Of course, there should also be a mechanism in place by the readers. —<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Messedrocker" class="mw-redirect" title="User talk:Messedrocker">harej</a> // <a class="mw-selflink selflink">change the rules</a> 18:16, 4 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Messedrocker-2009-01-04T18:16:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-04T18:16:00.000Z","author":"Messedrocker","type":"comment","level":2,"id":"c-Messedrocker-2009-01-04T18:16:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Messedrocker-2009-01-04T18:16:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules"></span></li></ul></li>
<li><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules"></span>Ban the use of plain external links <a class="external autonumber" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/">[1]</a> (like that) in main prose (one of my pet hates).</li>
<li>All regular editors should have a userpage.
<dl><dd>Why? -- <a href="/wiki/User:Gurch" title="User:Gurch">Gurch</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Gurch" title="User talk:Gurch">talk</a>) 13:49, 3 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z","author":"Gurch","type":"comment","level":2,"id":"c-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules","replies":["c-Majorly-2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z","c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:36:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Majorly-2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z"></span>Rightly or wrongly, a red userpage makes the person look like a brand new user. A redirect or blank page would be fine, just better than the red. I don't like seeing red. Especially in default sigs. <b><a href="/wiki/User:Majorly" title="User:Majorly"><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#6B8AB8">Majorly</span></a></b> <a href="/wiki/User_talk:Majorly#t" title="User talk:Majorly"><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:8pt; color:#6B8AB8">talk</span></a> 14:50, 3 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Majorly-2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z","author":"Majorly","type":"comment","level":4,"id":"c-Majorly-2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z","replies":["c-Gurch-2009-01-03T15:57:00.000Z-Majorly-2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Majorly-2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Gurch-2009-01-03T15:57:00.000Z-Majorly-2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z"></span>The problem with encouraging that is that it makes people associate 'userpage' = 'experienced user'. RC patrollers are particularly prone to this. And the situation there is bad enough as it is; several persistent vandals have learnt to create user and talk pages for their socks before using them maliciously -- <a href="/wiki/User:Gurch" title="User:Gurch">Gurch</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Gurch" title="User talk:Gurch">talk</a>) 15:57, 3 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Gurch-2009-01-03T15:57:00.000Z-Majorly-2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-03T15:57:00.000Z","author":"Gurch","type":"comment","level":5,"id":"c-Gurch-2009-01-03T15:57:00.000Z-Majorly-2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z","replies":["c-Majorly-2009-01-03T17:36:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T15:57:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Gurch-2009-01-03T15:57:00.000Z-Majorly-2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Majorly-2009-01-03T17:36:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T15:57:00.000Z"></span>Unless I know of the user (e.g. <a href="/wiki/User:JzG" title="User:JzG">User:JzG</a>, <a href="/wiki/User:Badger_Drink" title="User:Badger Drink">User:Badger Drink</a>), I assume a red page user is new. It's prejudiced I know, but that's how it is for <i>me</i> personally. I did say <i>regular</i> editors should create a userpage, not <i>every</i> user. Most do anyway. <b><a href="/wiki/User:Majorly" title="User:Majorly"><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#6B8AB8">Majorly</span></a></b> <a href="/wiki/User_talk:Majorly#t" title="User talk:Majorly"><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:8pt; color:#6B8AB8">talk</span></a> 17:36, 3 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Majorly-2009-01-03T17:36:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T15:57:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-03T17:36:00.000Z","author":"Majorly","type":"comment","level":6,"id":"c-Majorly-2009-01-03T17:36:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T15:57:00.000Z","replies":["c-Garden-2009-01-04T12:41:00.000Z-Majorly-2009-01-03T17:36:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Majorly-2009-01-03T17:36:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T15:57:00.000Z"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Garden-2009-01-04T12:41:00.000Z-Majorly-2009-01-03T17:36:00.000Z"></span>What about some sort of thing like autoconfirmed for userpage creation?  :D <a href="/wiki/User:Garden" class="mw-redirect" title="User:Garden"><font color="#33cc33"><b>Garden</b></font></a>. 12:41, 4 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Garden-2009-01-04T12:41:00.000Z-Majorly-2009-01-03T17:36:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-04T12:41:00.000Z","author":"Garden","type":"comment","level":7,"id":"c-Garden-2009-01-04T12:41:00.000Z-Majorly-2009-01-03T17:36:00.000Z","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Garden-2009-01-04T12:41:00.000Z-Majorly-2009-01-03T17:36:00.000Z"></span></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl>
<ul><li><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:36:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z"></span>I suggest un-learning that prejudice, rather than trying to force its effects onto other people.  I've been around a … <i>cough</i> … fair while on Internet, and I knew the perils of personal information on WWW pages long before Wikipedia even existed.  <a href="/wiki/User:Uncle_G/On_having_a_user_page" title="User:Uncle G/On having a user page">User:Uncle G/On having a user page</a> came up when I was nominated for administratorship.  When, much later, people here experienced problems with stalkers that resulted in their having to delete their user pages, I resisted the temptation to say "I told you so.".  Don't force people into a bad move simply because you want the colour red in an edit history or a log to mean something other than what it does mean: which is simply that a page linked-to does not exist. <a href="/wiki/User:Uncle_G" title="User:Uncle G">Uncle G</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Uncle_G" title="User talk:Uncle G">talk</a>) 04:36, 6 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:36:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-06T04:36:00.000Z","author":"Uncle G","type":"comment","level":3,"id":"c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:36:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z","replies":["c-Majorly-2009-01-06T10:02:00.000Z-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:36:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:36:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T13:49:00.000Z"></span>
<ul><li><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Majorly-2009-01-06T10:02:00.000Z-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:36:00.000Z"></span>Yes, I read your essay before, and it's a good one. But userpages, as I explain above, <i>do not</i> need any personal information on them. A blank page, a redirect - or even, just not mentioning any personal information on it would work. I simply dislike the broken link, the fact when it is clicked it causes the user page to go to edit mode, and it is a nowhere near as nice colour as blue is :-) <b><a href="/wiki/User:Majorly" title="User:Majorly"><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#6B8AB8">Majorly</span></a></b> <a href="/wiki/User_talk:Majorly#t" title="User talk:Majorly"><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:8pt; color:#6B8AB8">talk</span></a> 10:02, 6 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Majorly-2009-01-06T10:02:00.000Z-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:36:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-06T10:02:00.000Z","author":"Majorly","type":"comment","level":4,"id":"c-Majorly-2009-01-06T10:02:00.000Z-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:36:00.000Z","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Majorly-2009-01-06T10:02:00.000Z-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:36:00.000Z"></span></li></ul></li></ul></li>
<li><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Stifle-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules"></span>Delete <a href="/wiki/Template:Talkback" title="Template:Talkback">Template:Talkback</a>.</li>
<li>Ban the use of <a href="/wiki/Double_spaced_sentences" class="mw-redirect" title="Double spaced sentences">double spaced sentences</a>.  Yes, really.  Annoying aren't they?
<dl><dd>Not at all. HTML studiously ignores them when rendering :) <a href="/wiki/User:Stifle" title="User:Stifle">Stifle</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Stifle/wizard" class="mw-redirect" title="User talk:Stifle/wizard">talk</a>) 12:27, 3 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Stifle-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z","author":"Stifle","type":"comment","level":2,"id":"c-Stifle-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules","replies":["c-Majorly-2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z-Stifle-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Stifle-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Majorly-2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z-Stifle-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z"></span>It doesn't ignore them in the source code though. <b><a href="/wiki/User:Majorly" title="User:Majorly"><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#6B8AB8">Majorly</span></a></b> <a href="/wiki/User_talk:Majorly#t" title="User talk:Majorly"><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:8pt; color:#6B8AB8">talk</span></a> 14:50, 3 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Majorly-2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z-Stifle-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z","author":"Majorly","type":"comment","level":4,"id":"c-Majorly-2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z-Stifle-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Majorly-2009-01-03T14:50:00.000Z-Stifle-2009-01-03T12:27:00.000Z"></span></dd></dl></dd></dl></li>
<li><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Ipatrol-2009-04-05T23:12:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules"></span>Change the standard skin to Modern - it's neater than monobook imo. Userpages that have a banner on the top made in monobook look just dreadful in Modern :-(</li>
<li>Accept that IRC exists, is used, and is abused on occasion, but it isn't evil, and it is going to part of the project for a long, long time. There's nothing that can be done about it.</li>
<li>RFA is not broken, people are. No more perennial suggestions please!</li>
<li>Rename the Main Page to something out of article space.</li>
<li>Learn that Wikipedia is <i>not</i> just an encyclopedia, and meta discussion is, in fact allowed. No more "Go and write an encyclopedia!" comments in discussions please.</li>
<li>Discussions to ban disruptive users are not "lynch mobs". Anyone found calling it that will be banned forthwith :-)</li>
<li>Polls are not evil, people complaining about them are.</li>
<li>Editors of all ages are as welcome as each other, as long as they're a net positive. No ageism allowed!</li>
<li>Every admin should be a bureaucrat. Bureaucratship is not a big deal, and it would be even less so if they could reverse themselves with promotions.
<ul><li>I actually think the problem is that b'crats don't really have many rights. I would support giving 'crats the globalblock-whitelist right and removal of 'crat and admin groups right  to start.--<a href="/wiki/User:Ipatrol" title="User:Ipatrol">Ipatrol</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Ipatrol" title="User talk:Ipatrol">talk</a>) 23:12, 5 April 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Ipatrol-2009-04-05T23:12:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-04-05T23:12:00.000Z","author":"Ipatrol","type":"comment","level":2,"id":"c-Ipatrol-2009-04-05T23:12:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Ipatrol-2009-04-05T23:12:00.000Z-Majorly's_rules"></span></li></ul></li></ul>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2 ext-discussiontools-init-section"><h2 data-mw-thread-id="h-Peachey88"><span class="mw-headline" id="Peachey88"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-Peachey88"></span>Peachey88<span data-mw-comment-end="h-Peachey88"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:If_you_could_re-write_the_rules&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Peachey88"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"headingLevel":2,"name":"h-","type":"heading","level":0,"id":"h-Peachey88","replies":[]}}--></div>
<p>These are not so much proposed rules, but proposals to the pre-exising systems so they work better.
</p>
<ol><li>Simpler style guidelines
<ol><li>Cleanup MoS so is easier to understand for less advanced editors.</li>
<li>Reduce the number of subpages so content is easier to find</li>
<li>Have a common place for style guidelines (for example some WikiProjects store their own in their place and some contradict MoS standards)</li></ol></li>
<li>Make sure standards/documents don't contradict each other. An example of that is
<ol><li>WP:MOSNUM » "the first occurrence of each unit should be linked"</li>
<li>WP:OVERLINK » "It is generally not necessary to link... Plain English words, including common units of measurement".</li>
<li>A example of this issue can be seen at <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:ANI#Possible_Lightbot_Problem" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:ANI">Wikipedia:ANI#Possible Lightbot Problem</a> <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:Administrators%27_noticeboard/Incidents&amp;oldid=261669663#Possible_Lightbot_Problem">(Perma Link)</a></li></ol></li>
<li>Define some of the documentation meanings. Some of examples of this inculde:
<ol><li>"Common English"
<ol><li>What is common english?.</li>
<li>This "common english" could/would/does easier differ on the country its being taught in.</li>
<li>For example its common for me just to refer the temperature as 22 but that's not common in America because they use a different system, or i use the letter M for meters where as some locations don't and write it out fully.</li></ol></li></ol></li>
<li>Reduce locations of noticeboards for different matters (For example it can be hard for some less advanced users to find the correct one and they default to AN)<br/>Some of the noticeboards that i quickly found for users lodging complaints:
<ol><li><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Wikiquette_alerts" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:Wikiquette alerts">Wikipedia:Wikiquette alerts</a> aka WP:WQA</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Administrators%27_noticeboard/Incidents" title="Wikipedia:Administrators' noticeboard/Incidents">Wikipedia:Administrators' noticeboard/Incidents</a> aka WP:ANI</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Administrators%27_noticeboard" title="Wikipedia:Administrators' noticeboard">Wikipedia:Administrators' noticeboard</a> aka WP:AN</li></ol></li>
<li>Standardize Usernames for certain things. A example for this would be:
<ol><li>Bots » Most have the world in their username but some don't (Easier to notice on Recent Changes/Page Watchlist)</li></ol></li>
<li>Common sense when it comes to images. Sure a article does look nice with images but don't overload it and lay them out nicely.<br/>For example:
<ol><li>Don't go overboard, eg: as my IRC quote has already been shown by <a href="#Addshore's_Rules">AddShore</a> "The penis article doesn't need like 200+ images/examples" Sure it might benefit for a image or two and maybe a diagram but it doesn't need much more than that.</li>
<li>But there is a free version, we should use that instead. Free isn't always better, If theres a Fair Use image that identifies that image subject better than a Public Domain/GFDL one, i'm all up for using it.</li>
<li>Layout the images nicely, eg: <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Barney_(dog)&amp;oldid=252892209">(This)</a> looks worse than <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Barney_(dog)&amp;oldid=252892209">(This)</a>. Don't be afraid to move them into different sections, place them different sides of the page or even thumbnail them so they appear smaller.</li></ol></li>
<li>Ban the whole "Unwritten Rules" system, it just causes more problems and issues than its worth</li></ol>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2 ext-discussiontools-init-section"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONDESKTOP__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-Caulde-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-Caulde's_rules-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;replies&quot;:[&quot;c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:38:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules&quot;,&quot;c-Gurch-2009-01-04T12:59:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules&quot;,&quot;c-Caulde-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules&quot;],&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Caulde's rules&quot;,&quot;linkableTitle&quot;:&quot;Caulde's rules&quot;}--><h2 data-mw-thread-id="h-Caulde&#039;s_rules-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z"><span id="Caulde.27s_rules"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Caulde's_rules"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-Caulde's_rules-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z"></span>Caulde's rules<span data-mw-comment-end="h-Caulde's_rules-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:If_you_could_re-write_the_rules&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Caulde&#039;s rules"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"headingLevel":2,"name":"h-Caulde-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z","type":"heading","level":0,"id":"h-Caulde's_rules-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z","replies":["c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:38:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules","c-Gurch-2009-01-04T12:59:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules","c-Caulde-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules"]}}--><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-bar"><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-metadata"><!--__DTLATESTCOMMENTTHREAD__{"id":"c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:38:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules","timestamp":"2009-01-06T04:38:00.000Z"}__--><!--__DTCOMMENTCOUNT__8__--><!--__DTAUTHORCOUNT__3__--></div><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-actions"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONMOBILE__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-Caulde-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-Caulde's_rules-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;replies&quot;:[&quot;c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:38:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules&quot;,&quot;c-Gurch-2009-01-04T12:59:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules&quot;,&quot;c-Caulde-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules&quot;],&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Caulde's rules&quot;,&quot;linkableTitle&quot;:&quot;Caulde's rules&quot;}--></div></div></div>
<ul><li><b><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:38:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules"></span>CHU clerks to get new right(s) to rename</b> – the task is ridiculously simple and shouldn't be limited to just 'crats. Most clerks are well-experienced administrators and are aware of the relevant 'unwritten guidelines' which could be violated.</li>
<li><b>Username flagging</b> – implement a bot to automatically block all usernames which are deemed unacceptable after a 48-hour period (the time would begin after the leaving of a note regarding that on the respective user's talk page).
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Scunthorpe_Problem" class="mw-redirect" title="Scunthorpe Problem">Scunthorpe Problem</a> <a href="/wiki/User:Uncle_G" title="User:Uncle G">Uncle G</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Uncle_G" title="User talk:Uncle G">talk</a>) 04:38, 6 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:38:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-06T04:38:00.000Z","author":"Uncle G","type":"comment","level":2,"id":"c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:38:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:38:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules"></span></li></ul></li>
<li><b><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Gurch-2009-01-04T12:59:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules"></span>Cross-wiki administration</b> – allow all admins on commons and meta to automatically be administrators on the English Wikipedia.
<dl><dd>And vice-versa? -- <a href="/wiki/User:Gurch" title="User:Gurch">Gurch</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Gurch" title="User talk:Gurch">talk</a>) 12:59, 4 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Gurch-2009-01-04T12:59:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-04T12:59:00.000Z","author":"Gurch","type":"comment","level":2,"id":"c-Gurch-2009-01-04T12:59:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules","replies":["c-Caulde-2009-01-04T14:13:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T12:59:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Gurch-2009-01-04T12:59:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Caulde-2009-01-04T14:13:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T12:59:00.000Z"></span>Possibly. Commons would need an admin who is very familiar with image policy, though. <a href="/wiki/User_talk:Caulde" title="User talk:Caulde"><span style="color:#8B0000;font-weight:bold">Caulde</span></a> 14:13, 4 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Caulde-2009-01-04T14:13:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T12:59:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-04T14:13:00.000Z","author":"Caulde","type":"comment","level":4,"id":"c-Caulde-2009-01-04T14:13:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T12:59:00.000Z","replies":["c-Gurch-2009-01-04T14:15:00.000Z-Caulde-2009-01-04T14:13:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Caulde-2009-01-04T14:13:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T12:59:00.000Z"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Gurch-2009-01-04T14:15:00.000Z-Caulde-2009-01-04T14:13:00.000Z"></span>And Wikipedia would need an admin who is very familiar with <i>its</i> policies, too. You can't have it one way and not the other -- <a href="/wiki/User:Gurch" title="User:Gurch">Gurch</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Gurch" title="User talk:Gurch">talk</a>) 14:15, 4 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Gurch-2009-01-04T14:15:00.000Z-Caulde-2009-01-04T14:13:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-04T14:15:00.000Z","author":"Gurch","type":"comment","level":5,"id":"c-Gurch-2009-01-04T14:15:00.000Z-Caulde-2009-01-04T14:13:00.000Z","replies":["c-Caulde-2009-01-04T18:10:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T14:15:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Gurch-2009-01-04T14:15:00.000Z-Caulde-2009-01-04T14:13:00.000Z"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Caulde-2009-01-04T18:10:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T14:15:00.000Z"></span>Meta is fairly interchangeable with the English Wikipedia, whereas Commons admins have preference to working with images – most of the time, so I wouldn't see a reason why they would wish to change that. <a href="/wiki/User_talk:Caulde" title="User talk:Caulde"><span style="color:#8B0000;font-weight:bold">Caulde</span></a> 18:10, 4 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Caulde-2009-01-04T18:10:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T14:15:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-04T18:10:00.000Z","author":"Caulde","type":"comment","level":6,"id":"c-Caulde-2009-01-04T18:10:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T14:15:00.000Z","replies":["c-Gurch-2009-01-04T19:30:00.000Z-Caulde-2009-01-04T18:10:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Caulde-2009-01-04T18:10:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T14:15:00.000Z"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Gurch-2009-01-04T19:30:00.000Z-Caulde-2009-01-04T18:10:00.000Z"></span>So you'd give just Meta administrators adminship on this project? Or give Commons administrators adminship but only allow them to do image work? Or something else? -- <a href="/wiki/User:Gurch" title="User:Gurch">Gurch</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Gurch" title="User talk:Gurch">talk</a>) 19:30, 4 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Gurch-2009-01-04T19:30:00.000Z-Caulde-2009-01-04T18:10:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-04T19:30:00.000Z","author":"Gurch","type":"comment","level":7,"id":"c-Gurch-2009-01-04T19:30:00.000Z-Caulde-2009-01-04T18:10:00.000Z","replies":["c-Caulde-2009-01-04T20:10:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T19:30:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Gurch-2009-01-04T19:30:00.000Z-Caulde-2009-01-04T18:10:00.000Z"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Caulde-2009-01-04T20:10:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T19:30:00.000Z"></span>That's right for the meta administrators, however, for commons' they would have to be familiar with Wikipedia-specific policies as they are already familiar with so-called "etiquette" policies or what have you on commons. This would only be done upon request though and only stewards would enable the flagging of +sysop on the wiki, it would be quick and simple without the need for an RfA - only questions "proving" some kind of familiarity with process here will be asked to the user, no supports/opposes that sort of thing - but don't listen to me if you don't want to, this is just a wacky idea. <a href="/wiki/User_talk:Caulde" title="User talk:Caulde"><span style="color:#8B0000;font-weight:bold">Caulde</span></a> 20:10, 4 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Caulde-2009-01-04T20:10:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T19:30:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-04T20:10:00.000Z","author":"Caulde","type":"comment","level":8,"id":"c-Caulde-2009-01-04T20:10:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T19:30:00.000Z","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Caulde-2009-01-04T20:10:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T19:30:00.000Z"></span></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></li>
<li><b><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Caulde-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules"></span>Contacting users</b> – encourage users to set up a dedicated email account for Wikipedia-related activities; it cuts out all that about "How do you know my name?".</li>
<li><b>Remove future-class</b> – seems entirely obsolete to me; though I haven't seen the discussion regarding that yet.</li>
<li><b>Bureaucratic powers</b> – ditto what Biblio says above; I can't see a reason why not to.</li>
<li><b>Deletion policy preservation</b> – Leave policy on article deletion as it is, there is nothing wrong with it; unless any future situation(s) may require amendments.</li>
<li><b>Sourcing significance</b> – delete all articles without any sourcing, even if the event/place/person/thing is well-known.</li>
<li>May add more soon. <a href="/wiki/User_talk:Caulde" title="User talk:Caulde"><span style="color:#8B0000;font-weight:bold">Caulde</span></a> 17:57, 3 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Caulde-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z","author":"Caulde","type":"comment","level":2,"id":"c-Caulde-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Caulde-2009-01-03T17:57:00.000Z-Caulde's_rules"></span></li></ul>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2 ext-discussiontools-init-section"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONDESKTOP__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-Juliancolton-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-Juliancolton's_rules-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;replies&quot;:[&quot;c-Juliancolton-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z-Juliancolton's_rules&quot;],&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Juliancolton's rules&quot;,&quot;linkableTitle&quot;:&quot;Juliancolton's rules&quot;}--><h2 data-mw-thread-id="h-Juliancolton&#039;s_rules-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z"><span id="Juliancolton.27s_rules"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Juliancolton's_rules"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-Juliancolton's_rules-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z"></span>Juliancolton's rules<span data-mw-comment-end="h-Juliancolton's_rules-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:If_you_could_re-write_the_rules&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Juliancolton&#039;s rules"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"headingLevel":2,"name":"h-Juliancolton-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z","type":"heading","level":0,"id":"h-Juliancolton's_rules-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z","replies":["c-Juliancolton-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z-Juliancolton's_rules"]}}--><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-bar"><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-metadata"><!--__DTLATESTCOMMENTTHREAD__{"id":"c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:50:00.000Z-Realist2-2009-01-06T03:08:00.000Z","timestamp":"2009-01-06T04:50:00.000Z"}__--><!--__DTCOMMENTCOUNT__3__--><!--__DTAUTHORCOUNT__3__--></div><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-actions"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONMOBILE__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-Juliancolton-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-Juliancolton's_rules-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;replies&quot;:[&quot;c-Juliancolton-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z-Juliancolton's_rules&quot;],&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Juliancolton's rules&quot;,&quot;linkableTitle&quot;:&quot;Juliancolton's rules&quot;}--></div></div></div>
<ul><li><b><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Juliancolton-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z-Juliancolton's_rules"></span>Delete all articles lacking sources</b> –<a href="/wiki/User:Juliancolton" title="User:Juliancolton">Juliancolton</a> <a href="/wiki/User_talk:Juliancolton" title="User talk:Juliancolton"><sup style="color:#666660;"><b>T</b>ropical</sup></a> <a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/Juliancolton" title="Special:Contributions/Juliancolton"><sup style="color:#666660;"><b>C</b>yclone</sup></a> 20:35, 3 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Juliancolton-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z-Juliancolton's_rules"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z","author":"Juliancolton","type":"comment","level":2,"id":"c-Juliancolton-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z-Juliancolton's_rules","replies":["c-Realist2-2009-01-06T03:08:00.000Z-Juliancolton-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Juliancolton-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z-Juliancolton's_rules"></span>
<ul><li><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Realist2-2009-01-06T03:08:00.000Z-Juliancolton-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z"></span>Agree, sorry folks, but I do. — <a href="/wiki/User:Realist2" title="User:Realist2"><span style="color:#4173E4"><i><b>Realist</b></i></span></a><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Realist2" title="User talk:Realist2"><span style="color:#D80B0B"><sup><i><b>2</b></i></sup></span></a> 03:08, 6 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Realist2-2009-01-06T03:08:00.000Z-Juliancolton-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-06T03:08:00.000Z","author":"Realist2","type":"comment","level":3,"id":"c-Realist2-2009-01-06T03:08:00.000Z-Juliancolton-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z","replies":["c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:50:00.000Z-Realist2-2009-01-06T03:08:00.000Z"],"displayName":"Realist"}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Realist2-2009-01-06T03:08:00.000Z-Juliancolton-2009-01-03T20:35:00.000Z"></span>
<ul><li><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:50:00.000Z-Realist2-2009-01-06T03:08:00.000Z"></span>Deleting articles that lack sources is already <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Deletion_policy" title="Wikipedia:Deletion policy">Wikipedia:Deletion policy</a>.  You mean deletion of articles that <i>don't cite sources</i>.  That's a very different thing.  Careless conflation of the two has caused many problems for novices in understanding our policies and guidelines over the years.  <a href="/wiki/User:Uncle_G" title="User:Uncle G">Uncle G</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Uncle_G" title="User talk:Uncle G">talk</a>) 04:50, 6 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:50:00.000Z-Realist2-2009-01-06T03:08:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-06T04:50:00.000Z","author":"Uncle G","type":"comment","level":4,"id":"c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:50:00.000Z-Realist2-2009-01-06T03:08:00.000Z","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T04:50:00.000Z-Realist2-2009-01-06T03:08:00.000Z"></span>
<ul><li>Actually, I meant the article itself. Regardless of sources <i>available</i>, I believe that pages without citations should be dealt with properly, aside from simply sticking an ugly tag on it. –<a href="/wiki/User:Juliancolton" title="User:Juliancolton">Juliancolton</a> <a href="/wiki/User_talk:Juliancolton" title="User talk:Juliancolton"><sup style="color:#666660;"><b>T</b>ropical</sup></a> <a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/Juliancolton" title="Special:Contributions/Juliancolton"><sup style="color:#666660;"><b>C</b>yclone</sup></a></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2 ext-discussiontools-init-section"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONDESKTOP__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-Patton123's_rule-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;replies&quot;:[&quot;c-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z-Patton123's_rule&quot;],&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Patton123's rule&quot;,&quot;linkableTitle&quot;:&quot;Patton123's rule&quot;}--><h2 data-mw-thread-id="h-Patton123&#039;s_rule-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z"><span id="Patton123.27s_rule"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Patton123's_rule"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-Patton123's_rule-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z"></span>Patton123's rule<span data-mw-comment-end="h-Patton123's_rule-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:If_you_could_re-write_the_rules&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: Patton123&#039;s rule"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"headingLevel":2,"name":"h-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z","type":"heading","level":0,"id":"h-Patton123's_rule-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z","replies":["c-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z-Patton123's_rule"]}}--><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-bar"><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-metadata"><!--__DTLATESTCOMMENTTHREAD__{"id":"c-Iridescent-2009-01-20T23:26:00.000Z-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z","timestamp":"2009-01-20T23:26:00.000Z"}__--><!--__DTCOMMENTCOUNT__2__--><!--__DTAUTHORCOUNT__2__--></div><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-actions"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONMOBILE__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-Patton123's_rule-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;replies&quot;:[&quot;c-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z-Patton123's_rule&quot;],&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Patton123's rule&quot;,&quot;linkableTitle&quot;:&quot;Patton123's rule&quot;}--></div></div></div>
<ul><li><b><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z-Patton123's_rule"></span>Make abuse of <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:POINT" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:POINT">WP:POINT</a> bannable</b> it's "<i>do not disrupt</i> wikipedia to make a point", not "do not make a point". The number of times I've seen people interpret it the altter way is unbelievable.--<a href="/wiki/User:Patton123" title="User:Patton123"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="green">Patton</font></a><sup><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Patton123" title="User talk:Patton123"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="green">t</font></a>/<a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/Patton123" title="Special:Contributions/Patton123"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="green">c</font></a></sup> 23:17, 20 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z-Patton123's_rule"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z","author":"Patton123","type":"comment","level":2,"id":"c-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z-Patton123's_rule","replies":["c-Iridescent-2009-01-20T23:26:00.000Z-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z"],"displayName":"Patton"}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z-Patton123's_rule"></span></li></ul>
<dl><dd><dl><dd><small><i><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Iridescent-2009-01-20T23:26:00.000Z-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z"></span>[<a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a>]</i></small> – <i><a href="/wiki/User:Iridescent" class="mw-redirect" title="User:Iridescent"><font color="#E45E05">iride</font><font color="#C1118C">scent</font></a></i> 23:26, 20 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Iridescent-2009-01-20T23:26:00.000Z-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-20T23:26:00.000Z","author":"Iridescent","type":"comment","level":3,"id":"c-Iridescent-2009-01-20T23:26:00.000Z-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Iridescent-2009-01-20T23:26:00.000Z-Patton123-2009-01-20T23:17:00.000Z"></span></dd></dl></dd></dl>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2 ext-discussiontools-init-section"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONDESKTOP__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-Gurch-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-Res2216firestar's_rules-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;replies&quot;:[&quot;c-Gurch-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z-Res2216firestar's_rules&quot;,&quot;c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:10:00.000Z-Res2216firestar's_rules&quot;],&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Res2216firestar's rules&quot;,&quot;linkableTitle&quot;:&quot;Res2216firestar's rules&quot;}--><h2 data-mw-thread-id="h-Res2216firestar&#039;s_rules-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z"><span id="Res2216firestar.27s_rules"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Res2216firestar's_rules"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-Res2216firestar's_rules-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z"></span>Res2216firestar's rules<span data-mw-comment-end="h-Res2216firestar's_rules-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:If_you_could_re-write_the_rules&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: Res2216firestar&#039;s rules"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"headingLevel":2,"name":"h-Gurch-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z","type":"heading","level":0,"id":"h-Res2216firestar's_rules-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z","replies":["c-Gurch-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z-Res2216firestar's_rules","c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:10:00.000Z-Res2216firestar's_rules"]}}--><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-bar"><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-metadata"><!--__DTLATESTCOMMENTTHREAD__{"id":"c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:23:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:10:00.000Z","timestamp":"2009-01-06T19:23:00.000Z"}__--><!--__DTCOMMENTCOUNT__7__--><!--__DTAUTHORCOUNT__3__--></div><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-actions"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONMOBILE__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-Gurch-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-Res2216firestar's_rules-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;replies&quot;:[&quot;c-Gurch-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z-Res2216firestar's_rules&quot;,&quot;c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:10:00.000Z-Res2216firestar's_rules&quot;],&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Res2216firestar's rules&quot;,&quot;linkableTitle&quot;:&quot;Res2216firestar's rules&quot;}--></div></div></div>
<ol><li><b><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Gurch-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z-Res2216firestar's_rules"></span>"Second chance" unblock</b> I would allow blocked users a guaranteed second chance to be a good editor with an unblock, but if the bad faith editing or vandalism returned, the block would be back with no more chances.</li>
<li><b>Lower the threshold to pass an RfA</b> The current 70-75% support threshold is too high, it should be lowered to 60-65%.</li>
<li><b>More encouragement for new users to learn about editing Wikipedia</b> (formerly, "More restrictions on anon editing.) Here's an idea, let's put a big notice on top of the editing box for IPs and new users saying something like "Welcome to Wikipedia! Here are some pages to help you get started." Also move the link to the sandbox to above the edit box for new users and IPs. This would discourage test edits and help new users get started, and encourage IP editors to register an account.</li></ol>
<p>Most of the comments below are about a proposal that is no longer listed here. 
</p>
<ol><li><ul><li>Why? -- <a href="/wiki/User:Gurch" title="User:Gurch">Gurch</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Gurch" title="User talk:Gurch">talk</a>) 23:07, 3 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Gurch-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z-Res2216firestar's_rules"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z","author":"Gurch","type":"comment","level":2,"id":"c-Gurch-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z-Res2216firestar's_rules","replies":["c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Gurch-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z-Res2216firestar's_rules"></span>
<ul><li><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z"></span>Scratch that, I just generally think that IP editors are hard to distinguish between, not password protected, are the main source of vandalism, and therefore should have more restrictions.--<a href="/wiki/User:Res2216firestar" class="mw-redirect" title="User:Res2216firestar">Res</a><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Res2216firestar" class="mw-redirect" title="User talk:Res2216firestar">2216</a><a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/Res2216firestar" title="Special:Contributions/Res2216firestar">firestar</a> 21:03, 4 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z","author":"Res2216firestar","type":"comment","level":4,"id":"c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z","replies":["c-Gurch-2009-01-04T21:06:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z","c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T05:01:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z"],"displayName":"Res"}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-03T23:07:00.000Z"></span>
<ul><li><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Gurch-2009-01-04T21:06:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z"></span>True, but it seems odd to impose restrictions only on constructive contributors. Also, while anonymous users are the main source of vandalism, that doesn't mean it would go away if further restrictions were imposed. You could ban all anonymous editing, but that would just make new users the main source of vandalism, and so on -- <a href="/wiki/User:Gurch" title="User:Gurch">Gurch</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Gurch" title="User talk:Gurch">talk</a>) 21:06, 4 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Gurch-2009-01-04T21:06:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-04T21:06:00.000Z","author":"Gurch","type":"comment","level":5,"id":"c-Gurch-2009-01-04T21:06:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z","replies":["c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:13:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T21:06:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Gurch-2009-01-04T21:06:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z"></span>
<ul><li><ul><li><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:13:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T21:06:00.000Z"></span>Just IPs in general, I mean. I also think that a lot of vandalism is from people who want a quick spot on a popular website, and vandalism would go down if some well-placed restrictions were imposed. <a href="/wiki/User:Res2216firestar" class="mw-redirect" title="User:Res2216firestar">Res</a><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Res2216firestar" class="mw-redirect" title="User talk:Res2216firestar">2216</a><a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/Res2216firestar" title="Special:Contributions/Res2216firestar">firestar</a> 21:13, 4 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:13:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T21:06:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-04T21:13:00.000Z","author":"Res2216firestar","type":"comment","level":7,"id":"c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:13:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T21:06:00.000Z","replies":[],"displayName":"Res"}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:13:00.000Z-Gurch-2009-01-04T21:06:00.000Z"></span></li></ul></li></ul></li>
<li><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T05:01:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z"></span>The problem is that that preconception is just <i>wrong</i>.  There have been studies in the past concluding that editors without accounts are in fact the majority source of all of our content.  See also <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Administrators%27_noticeboard/IncidentArchive501#Anhydrobiosis" title="Wikipedia:Administrators' noticeboard/IncidentArchive501">Wikipedia:Administrators' noticeboard/IncidentArchive501#Anhydrobiosis</a>, where all of the editors without accounts were constructive contributors, quietly improving the encyclopaedia, all being reverted by the editor <i>with</i> an account.  This situation is not unique.  <a href="/wiki/User:Uncle_G" title="User:Uncle G">Uncle G</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Uncle_G" title="User talk:Uncle G">talk</a>) 05:01, 6 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T05:01:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-06T05:01:00.000Z","author":"Uncle G","type":"comment","level":5,"id":"c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T05:01:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Uncle_G-2009-01-06T05:01:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-04T21:03:00.000Z"></span></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ol>
<p><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:10:00.000Z-Res2216firestar's_rules"></span>Thought up a new proposal relating to the old one, check it out and let me know what you think.--<a href="/wiki/User:Res2216firestar" class="mw-redirect" title="User:Res2216firestar">Res</a><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Res2216firestar" class="mw-redirect" title="User talk:Res2216firestar">2216</a><a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/Res2216firestar" title="Special:Contributions/Res2216firestar">firestar</a> 19:10, 6 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:10:00.000Z-Res2216firestar's_rules"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-06T19:10:00.000Z","author":"Res2216firestar","type":"comment","level":1,"id":"c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:10:00.000Z-Res2216firestar's_rules","replies":["c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:23:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:10:00.000Z"],"displayName":"Res"}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:10:00.000Z-Res2216firestar's_rules"></span>
</p>
<ul><li><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:23:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:10:00.000Z"></span>Responding to Uncle G, my proposition was not based on the preconception you mentioned, I did not say that IPs are mainly the source of vandalism, I said that IPs are the main source <i>of</i> vandalism. I thoroughly believe that with enough thought and discussion, we can find a way to discourage vandalism while not discouraging constructive contributors.--<a href="/wiki/User:Res2216firestar" class="mw-redirect" title="User:Res2216firestar">Res</a><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Res2216firestar" class="mw-redirect" title="User talk:Res2216firestar">2216</a><a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/Res2216firestar" title="Special:Contributions/Res2216firestar">firestar</a> 19:23, 6 January 2009 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:23:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:10:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-01-06T19:23:00.000Z","author":"Res2216firestar","type":"comment","level":2,"id":"c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:23:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:10:00.000Z","replies":[],"displayName":"Res"}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:23:00.000Z-Res2216firestar-2009-01-06T19:10:00.000Z"></span></li></ul>
<ol><li><b>"IPBlock" userright</b> Many are saying that more admin functions should be opened to non-admins. One I would like to see is a userright allowing editors with the right to block vandalism-only IPs with less than +/- 50 or so edits for 24 hours or less.</li></ol>
<p>I will think up more and add them.
</p>
